textDelta: what is LDL? LDL is a "bad" cholesterol, and is associated with heart disease.

What lipoprotein is secreted from the liver? Lipoprotein is secreted from the liver in response to a variety of stimuli. These stimuli can include food, drink, exercise, or stress. Lipoprotein is important for the body to use up nutrients and to carry out other tasks.
What lipoprotein is secreted from the liver that is partially composed of dietary derived lipids? Plasma lipoprotein is secreted from the liver that is partially composed of dietary derived lipids.

what is chylomicrons? Chylomicrons are a type of white blood cell that is less common in adults but more common in children. Chylomicrons are important because they help to transport nutrients and oxygen to the body.
What is vldl? Voluntarily discontinued life support (VLS), also known as "death with dignity."
What is hdl? Hdl stands for “human readable text”, which is a type of file format used by websites to store and share text content.

What are types of primary lipoprotein? There are three main types of lipoprotein: LDL, HDL, andapo-Lipoprotein.

ops.insert: What did the Moscow Treaty on Strategic Offensive Reductions do?

textDelta: What did the Moscow Treaty on Strategic Offensive Reductions do? The Moscow Treaty on Strategic Offensive Reductions was a treaty that was signed between the Soviet Union and the United States on September 15, 1991. The treaty was designed to reduce the number of nuclear weapons in the world by up to 50%.

What does adding water do to PH? Adding water to a soil PH level can make it more acidic. This is because the more acidic soil has more available water molecules that can react with other elements to create acids.

ops.insert: A buffer is made from equal concentrations of a weak acid and its conjugate base. Doubling the volume of the buffer solution by adding water has what effect on its pH?

textDelta: A buffer is made from equal concentrations of a weak acid and its conjugate base. Doubling the volume of the buffer solution by adding water has what effect on its pH? The pH of a buffer is affected by the concentration of the acid and its conjugate base. If the buffer solution is made up of equal concentrations of a weak acid and its conjugate base, the pH will be the same. If the buffer solution is made up of more acid than its conjugate base, the pH will be lower than the acid concentration alone.

ops.insert: On a global scale, trends are suggesting that with rising incomes and urbanization we are seeing a rise in which food commodities?

textDelta: On a global scale, trends are suggesting that with rising incomes and urbanization we are seeing a rise in which food commodities? There is a rise in food commodities as incomes increase and more people are able to afford to buy food.

rising incomes and urbanization give rise in which food commodities? The rise in urbanization and the concentration of food commodities in cities give rise to a number of different food commodities. These include food items that are more expensive to produce, such as meat and dairy products, and food items that are more accessible, such as fruits and vegetables.

ops.insert: why do countries try to protect their own firms from exposure to the world market?

textDelta: why do countries try to protect their own firms from exposure to the world market? Some countries may try to protect their own firms from exposure to the world market for a variety of reasons. Some may do this to protect their own citizens, businesses, or industries from competition from other countries, or to protect their own economic stability. Other countries may do this to protect their own industries from being exported to other countries, or to protect their own economic stability.

What are some benefits of protecting our own firms from world markets? Some benefits of protecting our own firms from world markets are that we can better understand our own business and make better decisions, we can protect our own intellectual property, and we can better manage our own resources.
